questions.prompt: Texas-born novelist Patricia Highsmith's debut novel, Strangers on a Train, was published in 1950 and adapted to film by Alfred Hitchcock the next year, but she's likely even better remembered for her series of novels that feature what antiheroic, amoral psychopath?
